II. Key Points:  
1. Stacks follow the Last-In-First-Out principle and are suitable for bracket matching;  
2. Queues follow the First-In-First-Out principle and are suitable for breadth-first search;  
3. Deque (double-ended queue) offers higher efficiency.  
III. Application Associations:  
1. Stacks can be used to parse certain parameter files in simulation software;  
2. Queue concepts can be applied to handle project task flows.

